'''Liling Agessy''' (née '''Zedong'''; July 10, 1927 - July 29, 2014) was a Canadian and American professional volleyball player who spent most of her career playing for the Vancouver Vans from 1945 to 1959. She also played for the American teams Boulder Brownies from 1959 to 1964 and the Detroit Material Girls from 1964 to 1968. She won many awards throughout her career in both her home country and the United States. 

After retiring from volleyball, Agessy spent twenty years working as a marriage counselor from the early 1970s to the early 1990s. She then embarked on a political career spanning the last two decades of her life, whereas she served as a school board director and the mayor of her city. 

